## Pass 4: Draft

### 4.1 Section Plan

Map selected structure to sections with target word allocation:

| Section | Content | % |
|---------|---------|---|
| Opening | Per strategy; specific data in first 50 words | 10% |
| [Structure sections] | Evidence per pattern | 75% |
| Closing | Per strategy | 5% |
| Implications | Actions, recommendations | 10% |

### 4.2 Draft

Write section-by-section. Each section must:
- Lead with evidence
- Use citations inline `[ShortName, location]`
- Connect to branded concepts
- Follow metaphor system (if any)
- **Integrate across sources** (never "Document A says... Document B says...")

**Formatting**:
- Title: Content-specific, compelling
- L1 headings: Branded (not "Key Findings")
- Paragraphs primary; lists only when essential
- Bold key terms

