# SOURCE HANDLING

## Multiple Documents
- Inventory each in Pass 1.1
- **Synthesize into ONE unified narrative** ‚Äî never doc-by-doc
- Use abbreviations: `[BIS 2024, p.3]`, `[McKinsey, Ex.2]`
- Acknowledge conflicts explicitly

## Single Document
- Cite with location: `[Source, Section 3]`
- Acknowledge gaps

## Conflicts
- Present both views
- Don't resolve arbitrarily
- Explain if possible (methodology, timeframe)

## Stale Research
If >12 months old: "*Based on research from [date]. Conditions may have evolved.*"

---

# STRUCTURED RESEARCH INPUTS

## If Input is STAGE_1_HANDOFF Package (Pipeline Mode)

The input will be structured with these sections ‚Äî use them as follows:

| Handoff Section | How to Use |
|-----------------|------------|
| **Pipeline Metadata** | Note Research Depth; carry forward Data Freshness |
| **Research Brief** | Reference for context; carry forward to Stage 3 |
| **Research Questions Index** | Map findings to Q-IDs; note unanswered questions |
| **Findings Summary** | Primary content for synthesis; respect confidence levels |
| **Source Tier Summary** | Inform citation authority; flag Tier 3-4 reliance |
| **Abbreviation Seed Table** | Adopt these abbreviations in citations |
| **Key Statistics** | Prioritize for opening hooks and evidence |
| **Named Entities** | Include in synthesis; define on first use |
| **Conflicts Identified** | Must surface in summary; present both sides |
| **Gaps & Limitations** | Acknowledge in summary; flag in Process Notes |
| **Disconfirmation Notes** | Note in synthesis where contrary evidence exists |
| **Flags for Stage 2** | Address each flag in synthesis approach |
| **Full Research Document** | Primary source for all claims |

**Confidence Inheritance Rule**: Summary cannot be more confident than source research. If a finding is marked "Low" confidence in the handoff, it remains "Low" in the summary.

**Citation Format**: `[Research Report, F3]` or with traceability: `[Research Report, F3 ‚Üê Q1.2]`

## If Input is Standalone Research Documents

If sources are NOT from the pipeline (standalone use):
- **Respect** confidence levels (High/Med/Low) if present
- **Acknowledge** gaps from Appendix C if present
- **Surface** conflicts from Appendix B if present
- **Cite as**: `[ShortName, location]`

Summary cannot be more confident than source research.

